48 th session devops software installation all servers.

*web server
*app server
*db server

web server :

apt install update -y
apt install upgrade -y

apt install apache2 -y
cd /var/www/html/
git clone https://github.com/CleverProgrammers/pwj-netflix-clone.git
mv pwj-netflix-clone/* .
paste the public ip in new tab (to show the netflix application) and
uninstall apache2
sudo apt purge apache2* -y
            or
sudo apt remove --purge apache2 apache2-utils apache2-bin apache2.2-common -y
sudo apt autoremove -y

install nginx
apt install nginx -y
cd /var/www/html/
git clone https://github.com/CleverProgrammers/pwj-netflix-clone.git
mv pwj-netflix-clone/* .
paste the public ip in new tab (to show the netflix application) and
uninstall nginx
sudo apt purge nginx* -y
          or
sudo apt remove --purge nginx nginx-common -y
sudo apt autoremove -y
          


App server:

if my project java application?

apt install update -y
apt install upgrade -y
apt-get install default-jre -y
apt-get install default-jdk -y
java -version
apt install vim -y
vim /etc/profile.d/jdk11.sh
         export JAVA_HOME="/usr/lib/jvm/java-11.0.10"
         export PATH="$PATH:${JAVA_HOME}/bin"
echo $JAVA_HOME
echo $PATH
reboot   # reboot the server & restart

RUN BASIC JAVA PROGRAMME
 
vim HelloWorld.java

/* HelloWorld.java
 */

public class HelloWorld
{
        public static void main(String[] args) {
                System.out.println("Hello World!");
        }
}

cmd: javac HelloWorld  :to compile the progremme
cmd: java HelloWorld   : to execute the progremme




         PYTHON  INSTALLATION ON UBUNTU
if my project python application?

CMDS:
apt install update -y
apt install upgrade -y
apt install python3 -y
sudo apt install software-properties-common -y
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa -y
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3.8 -y
python3.8 --version
sudo apt install python3-pip -y
pip3 install numpy pandas
pip --version

python3  : this will take you to space where you can write your code
to exit the python  workspace ctrl+d




                             NODEJS INSTALLATION ON UBUNTU

if my project Nodejs application?

Install Latest Node.js via NodeSource (Recommended)
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y curl software-properties-common                #Install dependencies:
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_18.x | sudo -E bash -  #Add NodeSource repository for latest Node.js:
               or
sudo apt install nodejs -y     #Install Node.js and npm:
sudo apt install npm -y     #Install Node.js and npm
node -v
npm -v    #node package manager
 to run nodejs command use nodejs
console.log("Hello, my name is nandeesh")

 



               















